  "prompt": "What is the best way to use a simple past tense in a sentence?",
  "response": "Here are some tips for using simple past tense effectively:\n\n1. Basic structure\n\u2022 Use for completed actions in the past\n\u2022 Add \"-ed\" to regular verbs\n\u2022 Use irregular verb past tense form\n\n2. Examples of correct usage\n\u2022 \"I walked to the store yesterday.\"\n\u2022 \"She played tennis last weekend.\"\n\u2022 \"They visited Paris in 2019.\"\n\n3. Key indicators for simple past\n\u2022 Time expressions like:\n- Yesterday\n- Last week/month/year\n- Ago\n- In (specific year)\n\n4. Forming negative sentences\n\u2022 Add \"did not\" or \"didn't\" before the base verb\n\u2022 Example: \"I did not go to the party.\"\n\n5. Forming questions\n\u2022 Use \"Did\" at the beginning of the sentence\n\u2022 Example: \"Did you see the movie?\"\n\n6. Irregular verbs\n\u2022 Memorize unique past tense forms\n\u2022 Examples:\n- Go \u2192 Went\n- Eat \u2192 Ate\n- See \u2192 Saw\n\n7. Common mistakes to avoid\n\u2022 Don't mix tenses unnecessarily\n\u2022 Use consistent time references\n\u2022 Ensure verb agreement\n\nThe key is practicing and understanding when to use simple past tense appropriately.",
